2) I think one of the other most scary things would be for some cosmic catastrophe to set Earth on slow receeding course away from the sun, so that things gradually get colder and gloomier, and there is absolute certainty that it is just a matter of time before all life on Earth is extinguished.<br>
3) I think it would also be pretty scary to lay absolutely paralysed from head to foot at the foot of some desert crag and have huge vultures land around you and slowly converge on what they perceive as a lifeless corpse. I understand vultures consider eyes a particuar delicacy.<br>
